.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1668" width="2500"><media:credit>Department of Justice</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Cole Allen.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Cole Allen.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-Cole-Allen-rs-de57de.jpg" height="1668" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 18:18:15 GMT</pubDate><title>Judge apologizes over jail conditions to man charged in Trump assassination plot </title><updateDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 18:18:15 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:24:54 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A suspected hantavirus outbreak on a cruise ship has left three people dead and another person in intensive care. The ship is currently docked in the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of West Africa, and the operating company says passengers, including the two still on board believed to have the virus, have not been allowed to get off the boat. NBC’s Camila Bernal reports for TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-04T11:24:20.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_outbreak_260504</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/cruise-ship-hit-with-rare-hantavirus-outbreak-leaving-3-dead-262639685716</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_outbreak_260504/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Suspected Hantavirus Outbreak on Cruise Ship Leaves 3 Dead</media:title><media:player url="https://www.today.com/video/cruise-ship-hit-with-rare-hantavirus-outbreak-leaving-3-dead-262639685716"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1777893850346_tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_outbreak_260504_S3_1920x1080-5pbc07.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description ty